# Beads Task Tracking Rules

## The One Rule That Covers Everything

**`bd` is the single source of truth for all work items.** No exceptions.

---

## What Goes Where

| Content | Where it lives |
|---|---|
| Tasks, bugs, epics, spikes | `bd create` |
| AI planning docs, session notes, exploration output | `history/` directory |
| Project knowledge, decisions, handoffs | `memory/` directory |
| Source code | repo |

### Never

- ❌ Create markdown TODO lists (`TODO.md`, `TASKS.md`, checklists in any `.md` file)
- ❌ Use external issue trackers (GitHub Issues, Jira, Linear, Notion) alongside `bd`
- ❌ Duplicate tasks across systems — one task, one place, always `bd`
- ❌ Drop planning docs in the repo root — use `history/` or `memory/`

---

## Starting Work

```bash
# Always check this first — never ask "what should I work on?" without running it
bd ready --json

# Check what's already in progress (another agent may have started it)
bd list --status in_progress --json

# Claim before touching any code — mark yourself as the owner in the description too
bd update <id> --claim
```

`bd ready` shows tasks with no open blockers. If it returns nothing, create or unblock tasks before writing a single line.

### Claim coordination

When claiming a task, **append a note to its description** marking yourself as the active agent:

```bash
bd update <id> --description "$(bd show <id> --json | jq -r .description)

[Claimed by <agent-name> at $(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ)]"
```

**10-minute takeover rule**: If a task shows `in_progress` but its description has no claim note within the last 10 minutes, assume it was abandoned and take it. Verify with `bd show <id> --json` before proceeding.

---

## Creating Tasks

```bash
# Standard task
bd create "Title" -p 1

# Priorities: 0=critical  1=high  2=medium  3=low
bd create "Fix checkout crash on empty cart" -p 0
bd create "Add unit tests for auth middleware" -p 1
bd create "Improve error message copy" -p 3
```

### Always recommend the specialist agent in the description

Every task description must include a **Recommended Agent** line so the next agent knows who should pick it up without reading the whole description.

```bash
bd create "Add rate limiting to /auth/login" -p 1 \
  --description "Recommended Agent: security-test-engineer

Current state: /auth/login has no rate limiting; brute-force attacks are possible.
Target: max 5 attempts per IP per minute; 429 response with Retry-After header.
Verification: run k6 burst test, assert 429 after 5 rapid requests."
```

**Agent selection quick-reference:**

| Task type | Recommended agent |
|---|---|
| Test strategy, risk analysis, quality gates | `staff-test-engineer` |
| Test implementation, bug reports, flaky fixes | `junior-test-engineer` |
| Load / stress / capacity testing | `performance-stress-test-engineer` |
| Framework design, CI/CD test integration | `test-automation-architect` |
| REST/GraphQL/Pact contract tests | `api-contract-test-engineer` |
| OWASP, auth/authz, SAST/DAST | `security-test-engineer` |
| iOS/Android automation | `mobile-test-engineer` |
| Feature discovery, SFDIPOT, SBET sessions | `exploratory-test-engineer` |
| CI/CD pipelines, Docker/K8s, infra | `devops-engineer` |
| FastAPI, Pydantic, SQLAlchemy, backend | `backend-python` |
| PRDs, acceptance criteria, prioritization | `product-manager` |
| User flows, components, design tokens, a11y | `ui-ux-designer` |

### Link discovered work with `discovered-from`

```bash
bd create "Token refresh missing CSRF protection" -p 0  # → bd-c3d4
bd dep add bd-c3d4 bd-a1b2 --type discovered-from       # found while working on bd-a1b2
```

Every task discovered during another task must be linked — this creates a full audit trail.

---

## Programmatic Use (`--json`)

When AI agents parse `bd` output to make decisions, **always use `--json`**:

```bash
# ✅ machine-readable
bd ready --json
bd list --json
bd show <id> --json
bd list --status in_progress --json

# Parse with jq
bd ready --json | jq '.[].title'
bd ready --json | jq '.[] | select(.priority == 0)'

# ❌ never parse plain-text output
bd ready   # human display only — format may change
```

Use `--json` in any script, justfile target, or AI reasoning step that reads `bd` output programmatically.

---

## Completing Work

```bash
bd update <id> --status done

# Create follow-up tasks for anything discovered
bd create "Follow-up: ..." -p N
bd dep add <new-id> <done-id> --type discovered-from
```

---

## Landing the Plane (Session Completion)

Work is **not complete** until all steps below are done. Never hand off without finishing this checklist.

### Mandatory end-of-session workflow

1. **File `bd` tasks for any remaining or follow-up work** — nothing should live in your head or a scratch file.
2. **Run quality gates** — tests, linters, builds. Fix failures before pushing.
3. **Update task statuses** — close finished tasks (`--status done`), update in-progress items with notes.
4. **Sync Beads and push code** — in this exact order:

   ```bash
   git pull --rebase
   bd sync            # push Beads graph to remote so other agents see task state
   git push
   git status         # must show "up to date with origin"
   ```

5. **Update `memory/handoffs.md`** — replace your section with a ≤15-line summary for the next agent.
6. **Verify** — confirm all changes are committed AND pushed; nothing stranded locally.

### Critical rules

- **Work is NOT complete until `git push` succeeds**
- **NEVER stop before pushing** — that leaves work stranded locally
- **NEVER say "ready to push when you are"** — you must push
- **Always `bd sync` before `git push`** — keeps task graph and code in lockstep
- **If push fails**, resolve the conflict and retry until it succeeds

---

## Planning Output

Goes in `history/YYYY-MM-DD-<description>.md` — append-only, never in the repo root.

---

## Dependency Types

```bash
bd dep add <child> <parent>                         # child is blocked by parent (default)
bd dep add <finding> <source> --type discovered-from  # finding surfaced during source
bd dep add <dup> <original> --type duplicates         # dup is a duplicate of original
bd dep add <new> <old> --type supersedes              # new replaces old approach
```

---

## Summary

| Rule | Why |
|---|---|
| `bd ready` before every session | Never work on blocked or deprioritized items |
| `--json` always | Plain-text output format is unstable |
| Agent recommendation in every task | Next agent knows who to assign at a glance |
| Claim + 10-min takeover rule | Prevents two agents racing on the same task |
| `discovered-from` links | Full audit trail from any task to the work that surfaced it |
| `bd sync` before `git push` | Task graph and code stay in lockstep |
| Planning docs in `history/` | Keeps repo root clean |
| No markdown TODO lists | They go stale and duplicate `bd` |
| Land the plane | Nothing stranded locally; next agent has full context |
